You&#39;ll want to look at JPA tutorials on how bidirectional OneToMany and ManyToOne mappings work to help you out, but you should probably be using &#39;mappedby&#39; in your Rule-&gt;RuleUnitTest mapping:

      @OneToMany(mappedBy=&quot;rule&quot;, fetch = FetchType.EAGER)
      @Fetch(value = FetchMode.SUBSELECT)
      private List&lt;RuleUnitTest&gt; unitTests;

Also note that when deserializing JSON data, you will need to ensure that both sides of this relationship are set - or more importantly, that every RuleUnitTest.rule reference is properly set, since that is the relationship that owns (and so controls) the foreign key column value.

